I think technologically
the first question to...

81
00:05:09,966 --> 00:05:12,654
the first strategic decision
to make is,

82
00:05:12,961 --> 00:05:17,011
how to integrate new
infrastructures?

83
00:05:17,297 --> 00:05:20,972
New buses, new smart meters

84
00:05:21,536 --> 00:05:23,561
into the legacy infrastructures?

85
00:05:23,782 --> 00:05:26,907
How do you integrate
these kinds of things?

86
00:05:27,182 --> 00:05:28,570
On the financial side,

87
00:05:28,824 --> 00:05:33,361
it's of course the question of who
pays for the digital infrastructure?

88
00:05:33,576 --> 00:05:35,514
Who pays for the smart meters?

89
00:05:35,748 --> 00:05:38,098
Who pays for all kinds of devices

90
00:05:38,344 --> 00:05:41,744
and even the Telecom infrastructure
that is necessary?

91
00:05:42,281 --> 00:05:43,819
On the political side,

92
00:05:44,702 --> 00:05:49,577
one has to be aware of the
longterm impact of  these decisions.

93
00:05:49,821 --> 00:05:52,346
We are talking about infrastructure,

94
00:05:52,580 --> 00:05:55,805
so, whatever technology
is being bought or

95
00:05:56,031 --> 00:05:59,356
implemented will be there
for quite a long time.

96
00:05:59,565 --> 00:06:03,152
so it is important to make the right
strategic decision.

97
00:06:03,767 --> 00:06:05,155
On the social side, 

98
